	<section class="py-16 sm:py-24 xl:py-32">
		<div class="content-wrapper">
			<h3 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-balance 2xl:text-7xl">A Call to Action: Nature Under Pressure</h3>
			<p class="mt-8 text-xl">Despite its beauty, Scotland's nature faces significant challenges. Decades of intensive land use, habitat fragmentation, pollution, and the escalating climate crisis have taken their toll. We are now recognised as one of the most nature-depleted countries in the world.</p>
			<div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-8 sm:mt-16">
				<div>
					<h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Biodiversity Loss</h4>
					<p>Many iconic Scottish species, like the wildcat and capercaillie, are struggling. Habitats have become fragmented, making it harder for wildlife to thrive and adapt. The State of Nature Scotland report highlights alarming declines across many species groups.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Climate Change</h4>
					<p>Scotland is already experiencing the impacts of climate change, with warmer, wetter winters and more extreme weather events. Degraded ecosystems are less resilient to these changes and less able to help us mitigate their effects.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Habitat Degradation</h4>
					<p>Many key habitats are in poor condition. For example, a large percentage of our peatlands are degraded and emitting carbon, rather than storing it. Native woodlands cover only a small fraction of their potential area.</p>
				</div>
				<div>
					<h4 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Land Use Pressures</h4>
					<p>Competing demands on land, including agriculture, forestry, development, and recreation, can put pressure on natural habitats if not managed sustainably.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<p class="mt-8 text-2xl">Addressing these challenges requires bold action. Rewilding offers a hopeful and effective approach to tackling the interconnected climate and biodiversity crises head-on.</p>
		</div>
	</section>
